  <my:Details>
    <my:Ship />
    <my:Number>E 03</my:Number>
    <my:Date>2015-05-15</my:Date>
    <my:Title>Checking / Replacing / Handling Batteries</my:Title>
  </my:Details>
  <my:Hazards>
    <my:Hazard my:HazardId="1">
      <my:Description>Chemical - acid ingestion and or burns</my:Description>
      <my:Severity>3</my:Severity>
      <my:Likelihood>4</my:Likelihood>
      <my:RiskFactor>5</my:RiskFactor>
      <my:ControlMeasures>a) Crew training; 
b) Use of PPE - goggles, rubber gloves, protective apron, mask; 
c) When transporting batteries they should be kept in the upright position, handled by sufficient number of crew, consult also ‘Manual Handling’ Risk Assessment; 
d) Eye and skin wash liquids easily available.</my:ControlMeasures>
      <my:ReducedSeverity>3</my:ReducedSeverity>
      <my:ReducedLikelihood>1</my:ReducedLikelihood>
      <my:ReducedRiskFactor>3</my:ReducedRiskFactor>
    </my:Hazard>
    <my:Hazard my:HazardId="2">
      <my:Description>Electricity - short circuit or electrocution</my:Description>
      <my:Severity>3</my:Severity>
      <my:Likelihood>3</my:Likelihood>
      <my:RiskFactor>5</my:RiskFactor>
      <my:ControlMeasures>a) Use of PPE; 
b) Metal tools should not be come in contact with the batteries; 
c) Jewellery, wrists watches should be removed; 
d) Circuits to be switched off when connecting or disconnecting leads .</my:ControlMeasures>
      <my:ReducedSeverity>3</my:ReducedSeverity>
      <my:ReducedLikelihood>1</my:ReducedLikelihood>
      <my:ReducedRiskFactor>3</my:ReducedRiskFactor>
    </my:Hazard>
    <my:Hazard my:HazardId="3">
      <my:Description>Gas - explosive hydrogen</my:Description>
      <my:Severity>3</my:Severity>
      <my:Likelihood>3</my:Likelihood>
      <my:RiskFactor>5</my:RiskFactor>
      <my:ControlMeasures>a) Storage and work place should be well ventilated; 
b) Smoking or any open flame is strictly forbidden;
c) Metal tools should not be placed on top of the batteries (may cause sparking); 
d) Insulation of cables should be maintained in good condition; 
e) All battery connections should be kept clean and tight to avoid sparking and overheating; 
f) When working inside battery room gas proof lighting can only be used.</my:ControlMeasures>
      <my:ReducedSeverity>3</my:ReducedSeverity>
      <my:ReducedLikelihood>1</my:ReducedLikelihood>
      <my:ReducedRiskFactor>3</my:ReducedRiskFactor>
    </my:Hazard>
    <my:Hazard my:HazardId="4">
      <my:Description>Equipment - trapped finders or limbs</my:Description>
      <my:Severity>2</my:Severity>
      <my:Likelihood>3</my:Likelihood>
      <my:RiskFactor>4</my:RiskFactor>
      <my:ControlMeasures>a) Battery cover should always be secured when open; 
b) Doors from battery room should be secured when open.</my:ControlMeasures>
      <my:ReducedSeverity>2</my:ReducedSeverity>
      <my:ReducedLikelihood>1</my:ReducedLikelihood>
      <my:ReducedRiskFactor>1</my:ReducedRiskFactor>
    </my:Hazard>
  </my:Hazards>
